results.description:
Rhinos can only see two metres in front of them. If they see you, they’ll charge at you. This picture was taken from three metres away. These two baby rhinos were resting on a cool, wet morning in South Africa. I only had my iPhone on me, and we got as close as we could to the rhinos. When the one in front moved his head to look at us, we felt the ground rumble below our feet.

That was the moment I took this picture.
